'''大呼羅珊'''（Greater Khorasan; Middle Persian: Xwarāsān; Persian: خراسان‎, pronounced [xoɾɒːˈsɒːn] (About this soundlisten)。《[[遼史|遼史]]》異譯為'''忽兒珊'''，《回回館譯語》中称'''虎剌桑'''。<ref>https://archive.org/stream/02076762.cn#page/n6/mode/2up</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.huizucn.org/article-16-2.html |title=存档副本 |access-date=2015-12-30 |dead-url=yes |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150111000140/http://www.huizucn.org/article-16-2.html |archive-date=2015-01-11 }}</ref>，也稱為'''烏萇國'''<ref>{{cite book |last = Balogh |first = Dániel |title = Hunnic Peoples in Central and South Asia: Sources for their Origin and History |publisher=Barkhuis |isbn=978-94-93194-01-4 |page=104 |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=frnVDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA104 |language=en |access-date=2021-05-25 |archive-date=2020-11-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201119154010/https://books.google.com/books?id=frnVDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA104 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這是個歷史悠久的地區，構成古代[[大伊朗|大伊朗]]的東北行省。呼羅珊的名稱含意為“太陽之地”或“東部行省”。<ref name="Sykes">Sykes, M. (1914). KHORASAN: THE EASTERN PROVINCE OF PERSIA. Journal of the Royal Society of Arts, 62(3196), 279-286.</ref>{{NoteTag|a compound of ''khwar'' (meaning "sun") and ''āsān'' (from ''āyān'', literally meaning "to come" or "coming" or "about to come"). Thus the name ''Khorasan'' (or ''Khorāyān'' {{lang|fa|خورآيان|rtl=yes}}) means "sunrise", viz. "[[:wikt:Orient|Orient]], East".<ref>[http://www.ilssw.com/pages.php?id=10&cat=art Humbach, Helmut, and Djelani Davari, "Nāmé Xorāsān"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ilssw.com/pages.php?id=10&cat=art |date=20110102132819 }}, Johannes Gutenberg-Universität Mainz; Persian translation by Djelani Davari, published in Iranian Languages Studies Website.
MacKenzie, D. (1971). A concise Pahlavi dictionary (p. 95). London: Oxford University Press.</ref> The Persian word '''Khāvar-zamīn''' ({{lang-fa|خاور زمین}}), meaning "the eastern land", has also been used as an equivalent term.<ref>[http://www.loghatnaameh.com/dehkhodaworddetail-cbe368c6fbcf43b68107af29bc35fb45-fa.html DehKhoda, "Lughat Nameh DehKhoda"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.loghatnaameh.com/dehkhodaworddetail-cbe368c6fbcf43b68107af29bc35fb45-fa.html |date=20110718162055 }}</ref>}}

呼羅珊包括現代[[伊朗|伊朗]]領土的東北部、[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]部分地區、和[[中亞|中亞]]南部地區。這個地區曾被分為四個區塊。[[內沙布爾|內沙布爾]]（位於今伊朗）、[[梅爾夫|梅爾夫]]（位於今[[土庫曼斯坦|土庫曼斯坦]]）、[[赫拉特|赫拉特]]、與[[巴爾赫|巴爾赫]]（後兩城市在今[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]），這四座城市分別是最西，最北，最南和最東的四個區塊個別的中心。<ref name=Minorsky>Minorsky, V. (1938). Geographical Factors in Persian Art. Bulletin of the School of Oriental Studies, University of London, 9(3), 621-652.</ref>{{rp|645}}照嚴格的定義，呼羅珊往東僅延伸到[[阿姆河|阿姆河]]，但是根據比較寬鬆的說法，這個地名還包括[[河中地區|河中地區]]（現[[烏茲別克斯坦|烏茲別克斯坦]]的[[布哈拉|布哈拉]]和[[撒馬爾罕|撒馬爾罕]]）的大部分，<ref name=Minorsky/>往西延伸到[[裏海|裏海]]海岸。<ref name="Britannica">{{cite encyclopedia |url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/316850/Khorasan |title=Khorasan |quote=historical region and realm comprising a vast territory now lying in northeastern [[Iran|Iran]], southern [[Turkmenistan|Turkmenistan]], and northern [[Afghanistan|Afghanistan]]. The historical region extended, along the north, from the [[Amu_Darya|Amu Darya]] (Oxus River) westward to the [[Caspian_Sea|Caspian Sea]] and, along the south, from the fringes of the central Iranian deserts eastward to the [[Hindu_Kush|mountains of central Afghanistan]]. Arab geographers even spoke of its extending to the boundaries of [[Hindustan|India]]. |encyclopedia=[[Encyclopædia_Britannica|Encyclopædia Britannica]] Online |access-date=2010-10-21 |archive-date=2015-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150503223737/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/316850/Khorasan |dead-url=no }}</ref>以及[[卡維爾鹽漠|卡維爾鹽漠]]<ref name="lambton">{{Cite book|title=Continuity and Change in Medieval Persia: Aspects of Administrative, Economic and Social History, 11th-14th Century|url=https://archive.org/details/continuitychange0000lamb|last=Lambton|first=Ann K.S.|publisher=Bibliotheca Persica|year=1988|location=New York, NY|series=Columbia Lectures on Iranian Studies|page=[https://archive.org/details/continuitychange0000lamb/page/404 404]|quote=In the early centuries of Islam, Khurasan generally included all the Muslim provinces east of the [[Dasht-e_Kavir|Great Desert]]. In this larger sense, it included Transoxiana, Sijistan and Quhistan. Its Central Asian boundary was the [[Taklamakan_Desert|Chinese desert]] and the Pamirs, while its Indian boundary lay along the Hindu Kush toward India.}}</ref>，往南到[[信德|信德]]，<ref name="bosworth-eoi">{{cite book|last1=Bosworth|first1=C.E.|title=Encyclopedia of Islam, Vol. 5, Khe – Mahi |date=1986|publisher=Brill [u.a.]|location=Leiden [u.a.]|isbn=90-04-07819-3|pages=55–59|edition=New}}</ref><ref name=lambton />往東到[[帕米爾高原|帕米爾高原]]。<ref name=lambton /><ref name=Britannica /> 

[[薩珊王朝|薩珊王朝]]的[[喀瓦德一世|喀瓦德一世]]（在位期間公元488年到496年，在498年及499年曾被罷黜）或是其子及繼位者[[霍斯勞一世|霍斯勞一世]]（在位期間約531年到579年）的統治期間，（有可能是在公元520年之後）首度把帝國的東部和東北部劃分，而成立呼羅珊行政區域 <ref name="schindel">{{cite encyclopedia|title=Kawād I i. Reign|last=Schindel|first=Nikolaus|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/kawad-i-reign|encyclopedia=Encyclopaedia Iranica, Vol. XVI, Fasc. 2|pages=136–141|year=2013a|access-date=2021-05-25|archive-date=2020-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121225239/https://iranicaonline.org/articles/kawad-i-reign|dead-url=no}}</ref>

早期的[[伊斯蘭|伊斯蘭]]用法，經常把所謂的{{link-en|吉巴爾|Jibal}}或後來稱為{{link-en|波斯伊拉克|Persian Iraq|伊拉克阿賈米}}以東的的廣闊而鬆散的地區，甚至可能延伸至[[印度河|印度河]]谷和帕米爾高原，統稱為呼羅珊。以東和以西之間的邊界是[[戈爾甘|戈爾甘]]和[[赫卡通皮洛斯|赫卡通皮洛斯]]城市周圍的區域。特別是[[加茲納維德王朝|加茲納維德王朝]]、[[塞爾柱王朝|塞爾柱王朝]]和[[帖木兒王朝|帖木兒王朝]]將帝國劃分為“伊拉克”和“呼羅珊”地區。據信呼羅珊在西南部被沙漠和[[塔巴斯|塔巴斯]]小鎮定界，塔巴斯被稱為“呼羅珊之門”，<ref>Sykes, P. (1906). A Fifth Journey in Persia (Continued). The Geographical Journal, 28(6), 560-587.</ref>{{rp|562}}，從那裡向東延伸到阿富汗中部的[[興都庫什山脈|興都庫什山脈]]。<ref name="Britannica"/>從公元10世紀開始的資料，將興都庫什山脈南部的地區稱為呼羅珊邊區（Khorasan Marches），這個區域是呼羅珊和[[印度斯坦|印度斯坦]]之間的[[邊境|邊境]]地帶。<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|title=Hudud al-'Alam, The Regions of the World: A Persian Geography, 372 A.H. - 982 A.D.|last=Minorsky|first=V.|publisher=Oxford UP|year=1937|isbn=|location=London|pages=}}</ref><ref name="Baburnama" />

今天，大呼羅珊這個名字被用來稱呼更廣大的歷史地區，與現代的伊朗[[呼羅珊省|呼羅珊省]]（1906年到2004年）有所區隔，後者大致只佔具有悠久歷史的大呼羅珊的西半部。<ref>Dabeersiaghi, Commentary on Safarnâma-e Nâsir Khusraw, 6th Ed. Tehran, Zavvâr: 1375 (Solar Hijri Calendar) 235–236</ref>

